CONTEXT CONDENSING IN LANGCHAIN4J (PERSISTENT CHAT MEMORY)

OVERVIEW

This solution adds context condensing (conversation summarization) to a LangChain4j-based system using:

- MessageWindowChatMemory (sliding window)
- PersistentChatMemoryStore (MapDB persistence)
- Custom ChatMemoryStore decorator (CondensingChatMemoryStore)
- LLM-based summarization

The goal is to automatically compress long conversations while preserving important information.

------------------------------------------------------------
ARCHITECTURE

LangChain4j Memory Flow:

MessageWindowChatMemory (maxMessages = 10)
        ↓
CondensingChatMemoryStore (custom layer)
        ↓
PersistentChatMemoryStore (MapDB)

------------------------------------------------------------
HOW IT WORKS

1. LangChain4j keeps only the last N messages (window memory)
2. Messages are persisted in MapDB via ChatMemoryStore
3. When message count exceeds threshold:
   - older messages are summarized using an LLM
   - summary replaces old conversation history
   - recent messages are preserved

------------------------------------------------------------
IMPLEMENTATION: CONDENSING CHAT MEMORY STORE

public class CondensingChatMemoryStore implements ChatMemoryStore {

    private final ChatMemoryStore delegate;
    private final ChatLanguageModel summarizerModel;
    private final int threshold;

    public CondensingChatMemoryStore(
            ChatMemoryStore delegate,
            ChatLanguageModel summarizerModel,
            int threshold
    ) {
        this.delegate = delegate;
        this.summarizerModel = summarizerModel;
        this.threshold = threshold;
    }

    @Override
    public List<ChatMessage> getMessages(Object memoryId) {
        return delegate.getMessages(memoryId);
    }

    @Override
    public void updateMessages(Object memoryId, List<ChatMessage> messages) {

        if (messages == null || messages.size() < threshold) {
            delegate.updateMessages(memoryId, messages);
            return;
        }

        int keepRecent = 6;
        int splitIndex = Math.max(0, messages.size() - keepRecent);

        List<ChatMessage> oldMessages = messages.subList(0, splitIndex);
        List<ChatMessage> recentMessages = messages.subList(splitIndex, messages.size());

        StringBuilder input = new StringBuilder();
        input.append("Summarize the conversation. Keep key facts, decisions, preferences.\n\n");

        for (ChatMessage msg : oldMessages) {
            input.append(msg.toString()).append("\n");
        }

        String summary = summarizerModel
                .generate(UserMessage.from(input.toString()))
                .content()
                .text();

        List<ChatMessage> condensed = new ArrayList<>();

        condensed.add(SystemMessage.from(
                "Conversation summary so far:\n" + summary
        ));

        condensed.addAll(recentMessages);

        delegate.updateMessages(memoryId, condensed);
    }

    @Override
    public void deleteMessages(Object memoryId) {
        delegate.deleteMessages(memoryId);
    }
}

------------------------------------------------------------
SPRING CONFIGURATION

@Bean
ChatMemoryStore baseChatMemoryStore() {
    return new PersistentChatMemoryStore();
}

@Bean
ChatMemoryStore chatMemoryStore(
        ChatMemoryStore baseChatMemoryStore,
        OpenAiChatModel summarizerModel
) {
    return new CondensingChatMemoryStore(
            baseChatMemoryStore,
            summarizerModel,
            20
    );
}

@Bean
MessageWindowChatMemory messageWindowChatMemory(ChatMemoryStore chatMemoryStore) {
    return MessageWindowChatMemory.builder()
            .maxMessages(10)
            .chatMemoryStore(chatMemoryStore)
            .build();
}

------------------------------------------------------------
BEHAVIOR

- Old messages are automatically summarized when threshold is reached
- Recent messages are preserved verbatim
- Summary is injected as a SystemMessage
- Works transparently with AiServices
- No changes needed in ChatService

------------------------------------------------------------
BENEFITS

- Prevents context overflow
- Enables long-term conversational memory
- Works with persistence (MapDB)
- Compatible with LangChain4j AiServices
- Minimal architectural changes

------------------------------------------------------------
WHEN TO USE

Use this approach when:
- MessageWindowChatMemory alone is too limiting
- Conversations need long-term memory
- Token limits become an issue
- You want production-style memory management

